    "summary": "I hold a PhD degree in Applied Physics from the Eindhoven University of Technology with focus on photovoltaic technologies. I am strongly interested in what concerns functional materials for sustainable and renewable energy applications. \n\nMy main ambition is that of working for an impactful start-up that directly tackles urgent themes such as the need for novel technologies to fight and mitigate plastic pollution and climate change, as well as waste solutions to accelerate the transition to circular economy. \n\nThis dream also reflects on my private daily life, where I constantly watch my eating habits to reduce my carbon footprint, avoid plastic-packaged food, choose home electricity from green energy providers. To reconcile a plastic-free lifestyle with my 100% Italian love for pasta, I have systematically prepared delicious home-made fresh pasta over the last years.",
